article_title: U.S. Government Bonds Rally on Fed Outlook
article_text:
U.S. government bonds rallied along with stocks this week as the Federal Reserve’s hesitance to raise interest rates lifted financial assets broadly.

The yield on the benchmark 10-year Treasury note registered its first weekly decline in five weeks. The yield on the two-year note, highly sensitive to expected changed in the Fed’s rate outlook, logged the biggest weekly decline since October. Yields fall as bond prices rise.

U.S. government bonds rallied along with stocks this week as the Federal Reserve’s hesitance to raise interest rates lifted financial assets broadly.
The yield on the benchmark 10-year Treasury note registered its first weekly decline in five weeks.
